\end{array}

</math>


To compare with our 100.234 ¢ value, we'll have to convert this <math>G</math> to a <math>𝒈</math>, but that's easy enough. As we demonstrated earlier, simply multiply by <math>𝒋</math>:


<math>
𝒈 =

\begin{array} {ccc}
𝒋 \\
\left[ \begin{array} {rrr}
1200.000 & 1901.955 & 2786.314 \\
\end{array} \right]
\end{array}

\begin{array} {ccc}
G \\
